On Mon, 13 Sep 2004 10:49:04 -0400, Tom Emerson &lt;tree@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Take a cue from http://groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/message/865
&gt; I wrote (well, modified the URIRegexpfilter) a filter that can be used
&gt; to filter content types by regular expression. You can download the source
&gt; from
&gt; 
&gt; http://www.dreamersrealm.net/tree/source/ContentTypeRegExpFilter.java
&gt; 
&gt; To use it drop into /src/java/org/archive/crawler/filter, rebuild the
&gt; heritrix jar, and add org.archive.crawler.filter.ContentTypeRegExpFilter to
&gt; the end of src/conf/modules/filters.options.
&gt; 
&gt; Install the new jar and filters.options, restart Heritrix, and you can
&gt; now add the filter to the Writer.
